---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@/components/Section.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import Reveal from '@/components/Reveal.astro';
import Button from '@/components/Button.astro';
import Figure from '@/components/story/Figure.astro';
import { article } from '@/lib/schema';

import pawnStarsSet from '@/assets/story/mark-faith-filming-pawn-stars-uk-set.jpg';
import thankYouCard from '@/assets/story/four-rooms-thank-you-card-hobbit-first-edition.jpg';

const title = 'TV Appearances: Mark Faith on Four Rooms & Pawn Stars UK | Festival Art & Books';
const description =
  'Mark Faith has appeared as a rare-Tolkien expert on Channel 4’s Four Rooms and the UK version ' +
  'of Pawn Stars, showcasing first editions of The Hobbit and The Lord of the Rings.';

const trail = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'TV Appearances', url: '/tv-appearances' },
];

const schema = article({
  title,
  description,
  url: '/tv-appearances',
  datePublished: '2024-01-01',
  dateModified: '2026-06-25',
});
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} type="article" schema={schema}>
  <Section tone="midnight" space="md">
    <Breadcrumbs trail={trail} class="text-[var(--color-parchment)]/70" />
    <div class="mt-10 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr]">
      <Reveal as="div" mode="up">
        <p class="font-ui text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[var(--color-gold-300)]">On screen</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl leading-tight text-[var(--color-parchment)] sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          TV appearances
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose font-text text-xl leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-parchment)]/90">
          Mark Faith has brought rare-Tolkien collecting to television as a recognised expert,
          appearing on Channel 4’s Four Rooms and the UK version of Pawn Stars on the History
          Channel. On screen he showcased his complete set of the first ten Hobbit impressions and
          his Lord of the Rings first editions, the kind of pieces that have passed through his
          hands for over two decades.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
      <Figure
        src={pawnStarsSet}
        alt="Mark Faith being filmed at the counter on the set of the UK version of Pawn Stars"
        caption="Mark Faith filming on the set of the UK Pawn Stars."
        delay={120}
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section space="lg">
    <div class="prose-paper max-w-3xl">
      <Reveal as="div" mode="up">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] sm:text-4xl">
          Four Rooms (Channel 4)
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
          Four Rooms offers sellers of valuable and collectable items the chance to pitch to four of
          the UK’s biggest dealers (up to 30 dealers are rotated through the series, ranging from
          art collector and academic Ruth Meakin to interior designer and A-list dealer Celia
          Sawyer). Mark did not accept any offers for his Lord of the Rings first editions when he
          appeared, but later sold the set for £15,000. He also appeared trying to sell the first
          ten printings of The Hobbit (broadcast 1 June 2014).
        </p>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal as="div" mode="up" class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] sm:text-4xl">
          Pawn Stars UK (History Channel)
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
          Mark made two appearances on the UK version of Pawn Stars. The US original has run since
          2009 and is one of the most-watched shows in North America, drawing over five million
          viewers; the format depicts the bargaining over items customers bring in, with discussion
          of their historical background. The show has been broadcast in over 20 countries and won
          critical acclaim: DVD Town praised its cast and educational value, calling it “addictive”
          and a “big time winner.”
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
          Rodney Matthews and Mark Faith appeared on 9 September 2013, and Mark appeared again on 23
          September to showcase his rare complete set of the first ten Hobbit impressions, shown
          alongside Charlie Chaplin’s original tramp suit and the first Manchester United programme
          after the Munich air crash. As the show put it: “…the boys meet a seller looking to part
          with ten first editions of the J.R.R. Tolkien classic, The Hobbit. The seller’s asking big
          money for his books, but does the price ring true for this precious literary classic?”
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
          On Pawn Stars, Mark also tried to sell Rodney Matthews pencil sketches used for the book
          Alice’s Adventures in Wonderland, an episode that also features an appearance by Rodney
          Matthews.
        </p>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal as="div" mode="up" class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-[var(--color-midnight-900)] sm:text-4xl">
          More media
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]">
          A first-edition Hobbit handled by Mark also featured on ITV’s Masterpiece with Alan
          Titchmarsh, filmed at Kentwell Hall in Suffolk. Past clips are collected on Mark’s YouTube
          channel.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-text text-base text-[var(--color-muted)]">
          {/* TODO: Mark to confirm which episode links can be embedded — some Four Rooms clips
              may be restricted for copyright reasons. */}
        </p>
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal as="div" mode="up" class="mt-8">
        <Figure
          src={thankYouCard}
          alt="Autographed thank-you card from a TV production for the use of Mark Faith's first-edition Hobbit"
          caption="A production’s handwritten thank-you for the use of Mark’s first-edition Hobbit."
          delay={80}
        />
      </Reveal>

      <Reveal as="div" mode="up" class="mt-10 not-prose">
        <p class="font-text text-lg text-[var(--color-text)]">
          As a new cycle of Tolkien film and events begins, Mark plans to do more television and
          media. (We stopped before because most producers do not pay participants for their time
          and expenses; producers willing to cover an expert’s time are welcome to get in touch.)
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <Button href="https://www.youtube.com/c/MarkFaithD52" variant="gold">Watch on YouTube</Button>
          <Button href="/news-media" variant="ghost">Press &amp; media</Button>
          <Button href="/contact" variant="ghost">Contact Mark</Button>
        </div>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
